Heat the oil in a frying pan over a medium heat and fry the onion and garlic for 2-3 minutes, until softened.Add the lamb slices and stir-fry for 1-2 minutes.Add the chilli flakes, sesame oil, soy sauce, tomato ketchup, sesame seeds and honey. Stir-fry until the lamb is completely cooked through, then season, to taste, with salt and freshly ground black pepper.To serve, place the stir fry onto a plate and sprinkle with chives.